    <item>
      <title>MIDI &amp; Audio Recorder</title>
      <link>https://danialrami.com/posts/midi-audio-recorder/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 07 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://danialrami.com/posts/midi-audio-recorder/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve wanted a tool like this for years, because I&amp;rsquo;ve always found myself sitting at my piano and wishing that with one button I could very easily record a jam. Something way more pared down than a daw, with less setup time and complexity, and that won&amp;rsquo;t tempt me to start piling on effects.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://danialrami.com/images/Screenshot%202025-01-16%20at%201.08.23%20PM.png&#34; alt=&#34;Image Description&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;field-recorder-on-steroids&#34;&gt;Field Recorder on Steroids&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Taking inspiration from the simplicity of tape machines and field recorders, I wanted to create a modern hybrid that could capture both audio and MIDI simultaneously. The goal was to preserve that spontaneous &amp;ldquo;just hit record&amp;rdquo; feeling while adding the flexibility of digital recording.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
